## ğŸ§‘ğŸ¾â€ğŸ« what this challenge teaches u
how to hijack a command by placing a custom script earlier in the PATH  
in this case, we hijacked the rm command by replacing it w/ a script that prints the flag
to make it work, it was necessary to ensure that the directory containing our fake rm came first in the PATH variable,
so that the real rm command would not be called instead

